<HEADLINE>
China targets corruption among fire-fighting officials
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, Nov. 13 (Xinhua)
</P>
<P>
Chinese fire-fighting officials and their spouse and children are
banned from running companies related to fire-fighting facilities
and fire protection materials, according a new regulation issued
Monday.
</P>
<P>
They are also prohibited from providing fire protection services,
said the regulation issued by the Fire Bureau under the Ministry
of Public Security (MPS) to combat corruption among fire-fighting
forces.
</P>
<P>
It prohibited officials from taking advantage of their posts for
illegal profit in fire prevention inspection and approvals for
construction projects, fire accident investigations and
supervision of fire-fighting facilities.
</P>
<P>
They are also forbidden from taking bribes in construction
projects related to the force, material purchasing, in the
appointment and removal of officials, personnel transfer and
promotion, and new member recruitment, the regulation noted.
</P>
<P>
Those who violate the regulation will be seriously punished in
accordance with the law and expelled from the force, it said.
</P>
